{
  "texts": [
    "(4) Action impact: what are the consequences of the actions?",
    "Among these perspectives, the first two focus on the aspects preceding the action (\"before-action\" aspects), the third focuses on the action itself (\"in-action\" aspect), and the fourth emphasizes the impact of the actions (\"after-action\" aspect).Action goal: The agent can perform actions with various objectives.",
    "Here, we present several representative examples:(1) Task Completion.",
    "In this scenario, the agent's actions are aimed at accomplishing specific tasks, such as crafting an iron pickaxe in Minecraft [38] or completing a function in software development [18].",
    "These actions usually have well-defined objectives, and each action contributes to the completion of the final task."
  ]
}